Global Radiative Cooling Material Market Insights
Radiative Cooling Material Market size was valued at USD 1.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 4.2 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 15.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Radiative Cooling Material Market Overview
The global radiative cooling material market was valued at USD 1.4 billion in 2023 and is projected to reach USD 2.8 billion by 2030, expanding at a CAGR of 10.3% from 2024 to 2030. This market growth is driven by the increasing demand for energy-efficient solutions and sustainable building materials. Radiative cooling materials are becoming vital in combating urban heat islands and reducing the dependency on traditional air-conditioning systems. The technology’s ability to reflect sunlight while emitting infrared radiation to cool the surface naturally has opened new opportunities across various industries, including construction, automotive, and electronics. Additionally, government regulations promoting green buildings are further supporting the market's expansion.

